{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"So it's 1995,"},{"time":3000,"text":"I'm in college,"},{"time":5000,"text":"and a friend and I go on a road trip"},{"time":8000,"text":"from Providence, Rhode Island"},{"time":10000,"text":"to Portland, Oregon."},{"time":12000,"text":"And you know, we're young and unemployed,"},{"time":15000,"text":"so we do the whole thing on back roads"},{"time":17000,"text":"through state parks"},{"time":19000,"text":"and national forests --"},{"time":22000,"text":"basically the longest route we can possibly take."},{"time":26000,"text":"And somewhere in the middle of South Dakota,"},{"time":29000,"text":"I turn to my friend"},{"time":32000,"text":"and I ask her a question"},{"time":34000,"text":"that's been bothering me"},{"time":36000,"text":"for 2,000 miles."},{"time":40000,"text":"\"What's up with the Chinese character I keep seeing by the side of the road?\""},{"time":47000,"text":"My friend looks at me totally blankly."},{"time":51000,"text":"There's actually a gentleman in the front row"},{"time":53000,"text":"who's doing a perfect imitation of her look."},{"time":56000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":59000,"text":"And I'm like, \"You know,"},{"time":61000,"text":"all the signs we keep seeing"},{"time":63000,"text":"with the Chinese character on them.\""},{"time":67000,"text":"She just stares at me for a few moments,"},{"time":70000,"text":"and then she cracks up,"},{"time":73000,"text":"because she figures out what I'm talking about."},{"time":75000,"text":"And what I'm talking about is this."},{"time":78000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":84000,"text":"Right, the famous Chinese character for picnic area."}]},{"cues":[{"time":88000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":90000,"text":"I've spent the last five years of my life"},{"time":94000,"text":"thinking about situations"},{"time":96000,"text":"exactly like this --"},{"time":99000,"text":"why we sometimes misunderstand"},{"time":101000,"text":"the signs around us,"},{"time":103000,"text":"and how we behave when that happens,"},{"time":106000,"text":"and what all of this can tell us about human nature."},{"time":110000,"text":"In other words, as you heard Chris say,"},{"time":112000,"text":"I've spent the last five years"},{"time":114000,"text":"thinking about being wrong."},{"time":117000,"text":"This might strike you as a strange career move,"},{"time":120000,"text":"but it actually has one great advantage:"},{"time":123000,"text":"no job competition."},{"time":125000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":127000,"text":"In fact, most of us do everything we can"},{"time":130000,"text":"to avoid thinking about being wrong,"},{"time":133000,"text":"or at least to avoid thinking about the possibility"},{"time":135000,"text":"that we ourselves are wrong."},{"time":137000,"text":"We get it in the abstract."},{"time":139000,"text":"We all know everybody in this room makes mistakes."},{"time":142000,"text":"The human species, in general, is fallible -- okay fine."}]},{"cues":[{"time":146000,"text":"But when it comes down to me, right now,"},{"time":149000,"text":"to all the beliefs I hold,"},{"time":151000,"text":"here in the present tense,"},{"time":154000,"text":"suddenly all of this abstract appreciation of fallibility"},{"time":158000,"text":"goes out the window --"},{"time":161000,"text":"and I can't actually think of anything I'm wrong about."},{"time":165000,"text":"And the thing is, the present tense is where we live."},{"time":168000,"text":"We go to meetings in the present tense;"},{"time":171000,"text":"we go on family vacations in the present tense;"},{"time":173000,"text":"we go to the polls and vote in the present tense."},{"time":177000,"text":"So effectively, we all kind of wind up traveling through life,"},{"time":180000,"text":"trapped in this little bubble"},{"time":182000,"text":"of feeling very right about everything."}]},{"cues":[{"time":186000,"text":"I think this is a problem."},{"time":188000,"text":"I think it's a problem for each of us as individuals,"},{"time":191000,"text":"in our personal and professional lives,"},{"time":194000,"text":"and I think it's a problem for all of us collectively as a culture."},{"time":197000,"text":"So what I want to do today"},{"time":199000,"text":"is, first of all, talk about why we get stuck"},{"time":202000,"text":"inside this feeling of being right."},{"time":204000,"text":"And second, why it's such a problem."},{"time":207000,"text":"And finally, I want to convince you"},{"time":209000,"text":"that it is possible"},{"time":211000,"text":"to step outside of that feeling"},{"time":213000,"text":"and that if you can do so,"},{"time":215000,"text":"it is the single greatest"},{"time":217000,"text":"moral, intellectual and creative leap you can make."}]},{"cues":[{"time":222000,"text":"So why do we get stuck"},{"time":224000,"text":"in this feeling of being right?"},{"time":226000,"text":"One reason, actually, has to do with a feeling of being wrong."},{"time":229000,"text":"So let me ask you guys something --"},{"time":231000,"text":"or actually, let me ask you guys something, because you're right here:"},{"time":235000,"text":"How does it feel -- emotionally --"},{"time":238000,"text":"how does it feel to be wrong?"},{"time":241000,"text":"Dreadful. Thumbs down."},{"time":244000,"text":"Embarrassing. Okay, wonderful, great."},{"time":246000,"text":"Dreadful, thumbs down, embarrassing --"},{"time":248000,"text":"thank you, these are great answers,"},{"time":251000,"text":"but they're answers to a different question."},{"time":254000,"text":"You guys are answering the question:"},{"time":256000,"text":"How does it feel to realize you're wrong?"},{"time":259000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":263000,"text":"Realizing you're wrong can feel like all of that and a lot of other things, right?"},{"time":266000,"text":"I mean it can be devastating, it can be revelatory,"},{"time":269000,"text":"it can actually be quite funny,"},{"time":271000,"text":"like my stupid Chinese character mistake."},{"time":274000,"text":"But just being wrong"},{"time":277000,"text":"doesn't feel like anything."}]},{"cues":[{"time":279000,"text":"I'll give you an analogy."},{"time":282000,"text":"Do you remember that Loony Tunes cartoon"},{"time":284000,"text":"where there's this pathetic coyote"},{"time":286000,"text":"who's always chasing and never catching a roadrunner?"},{"time":288000,"text":"In pretty much every episode of this cartoon,"},{"time":291000,"text":"there's a moment where the coyote is chasing the roadrunner"},{"time":293000,"text":"and the roadrunner runs off a cliff,"},{"time":295000,"text":"which is fine -- he's a bird, he can fly."},{"time":298000,"text":"But the thing is, the coyote runs off the cliff right after him."},{"time":302000,"text":"And what's funny --"},{"time":304000,"text":"at least if you're six years old --"},{"time":306000,"text":"is that the coyote's totally fine too."},{"time":308000,"text":"He just keeps running --"},{"time":310000,"text":"right up until the moment that he looks down"},{"time":312000,"text":"and realizes that he's in mid-air."},{"time":315000,"text":"That's when he falls."},{"time":319000,"text":"When we're wrong about something --"},{"time":321000,"text":"not when we realize it, but before that --"},{"time":324000,"text":"we're like that coyote"},{"time":327000,"text":"after he's gone off the cliff and before he looks down."},{"time":331000,"text":"You know, we're already wrong,"},{"time":334000,"text":"we're already in trouble,"},{"time":336000,"text":"but we feel like we're on solid ground."},{"time":340000,"text":"So I should actually correct something I said a moment ago."},{"time":343000,"text":"It does feel like something to be wrong;"},{"time":346000,"text":"it feels like being right."}]},{"cues":[{"time":349000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":352000,"text":"So this is one reason, a structural reason,"},{"time":355000,"text":"why we get stuck inside this feeling of rightness."},{"time":357000,"text":"I call this error blindness."},{"time":359000,"text":"Most of the time,"},{"time":361000,"text":"we don't have any kind of internal cue"},{"time":364000,"text":"to let us know that we're wrong about something,"},{"time":366000,"text":"until it's too late."},{"time":369000,"text":"But there's a second reason that we get stuck inside this feeling as well --"},{"time":372000,"text":"and this one is cultural."},{"time":375000,"text":"Think back for a moment to elementary school."},{"time":378000,"text":"You're sitting there in class,"},{"time":380000,"text":"and your teacher is handing back quiz papers,"},{"time":383000,"text":"and one of them looks like this."},{"time":385000,"text":"This is not mine, by the way."},{"time":387000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":389000,"text":"So there you are in grade school,"},{"time":392000,"text":"and you know exactly what to think"},{"time":394000,"text":"about the kid who got this paper."},{"time":397000,"text":"It's the dumb kid, the troublemaker,"},{"time":400000,"text":"the one who never does his homework."},{"time":403000,"text":"So by the time you are nine years old,"},{"time":406000,"text":"you've already learned, first of all,"},{"time":408000,"text":"that people who get stuff wrong"},{"time":410000,"text":"are lazy, irresponsible dimwits --"},{"time":413000,"text":"and second of all,"},{"time":415000,"text":"that the way to succeed in life"},{"time":417000,"text":"is to never make any mistakes."}]},{"cues":[{"time":421000,"text":"We learn these really bad lessons really well."},{"time":426000,"text":"And a lot of us --"},{"time":428000,"text":"and I suspect, especially a lot of us in this room --"},{"time":432000,"text":"deal with them by just becoming"},{"time":434000,"text":"perfect little A students,"},{"time":436000,"text":"perfectionists, over-achievers."},{"time":439000,"text":"Right,"},{"time":441000,"text":"Mr. CFO, astrophysicist, ultra-marathoner?"},{"time":445000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":452000,"text":"You're all CFO, astrophysicists, ultra-marathoners, it turns out."},{"time":456000,"text":"Okay, so fine."},{"time":458000,"text":"Except that then we freak out"},{"time":461000,"text":"at the possibility that we've gotten something wrong."},{"time":463000,"text":"Because according to this,"},{"time":466000,"text":"getting something wrong"},{"time":468000,"text":"means there's something wrong with us."},{"time":471000,"text":"So we just insist that we're right,"},{"time":473000,"text":"because it makes us feel smart and responsible"},{"time":475000,"text":"and virtuous and safe."}]},{"cues":[{"time":479000,"text":"So let me tell you a story."},{"time":481000,"text":"A couple of years ago,"},{"time":483000,"text":"a woman comes into Beth Israel Deaconess Medical Center for a surgery."},{"time":486000,"text":"Beth Israel's in Boston."},{"time":488000,"text":"It's the teaching hospital for Harvard --"},{"time":490000,"text":"one of the best hospitals in the country."},{"time":492000,"text":"So this woman comes in and she's taken into the operating room."},{"time":495000,"text":"She's anesthetized, the surgeon does his thing --"},{"time":497000,"text":"stitches her back up, sends her out to the recovery room."},{"time":500000,"text":"Everything seems to have gone fine."},{"time":503000,"text":"And she wakes up, and she looks down at herself,"},{"time":506000,"text":"and she says, \"Why is the wrong side of my body in bandages?\""},{"time":510000,"text":"Well the wrong side of her body is in bandages"},{"time":513000,"text":"because the surgeon has performed a major operation"},{"time":515000,"text":"on her left leg instead of her right one."},{"time":519000,"text":"When the vice president for health care quality at Beth Israel"},{"time":522000,"text":"spoke about this incident,"},{"time":525000,"text":"he said something very interesting."},{"time":528000,"text":"He said, \"For whatever reason,"},{"time":531000,"text":"the surgeon simply felt"},{"time":533000,"text":"that he was on the correct side of the patient.\""},{"time":535000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":540000,"text":"The point of this story"},{"time":542000,"text":"is that trusting too much in the feeling"},{"time":545000,"text":"of being on the correct side of anything"},{"time":548000,"text":"can be very dangerous."}]},{"cues":[{"time":551000,"text":"This internal sense of rightness"},{"time":554000,"text":"that we all experience so often"},{"time":556000,"text":"is not a reliable guide"},{"time":558000,"text":"to what is actually going on in the external world."},{"time":561000,"text":"And when we act like it is,"},{"time":563000,"text":"and we stop entertaining the possibility that we could be wrong,"},{"time":567000,"text":"well that's when we end up doing things"},{"time":569000,"text":"like dumping 200 million gallons of oil into the Gulf of Mexico,"},{"time":573000,"text":"or torpedoing the global economy."},{"time":577000,"text":"So this is a huge practical problem."},{"time":580000,"text":"But it's also a huge social problem."}]},{"cues":[{"time":583000,"text":"Think for a moment about what it means to feel right."},{"time":587000,"text":"It means that you think that your beliefs"},{"time":589000,"text":"just perfectly reflect reality."},{"time":592000,"text":"And when you feel that way,"},{"time":594000,"text":"you've got a problem to solve,"},{"time":596000,"text":"which is, how are you going to explain"},{"time":598000,"text":"all of those people who disagree with you?"},{"time":601000,"text":"It turns out, most of us explain those people the same way,"},{"time":604000,"text":"by resorting to a series of unfortunate assumptions."},{"time":608000,"text":"The first thing we usually do when someone disagrees with us"},{"time":611000,"text":"is we just assume they're ignorant."},{"time":614000,"text":"They don't have access to the same information that we do,"},{"time":616000,"text":"and when we generously share that information with them,"},{"time":619000,"text":"they're going to see the light and come on over to our team."},{"time":622000,"text":"When that doesn't work,"},{"time":625000,"text":"when it turns out those people have all the same facts that we do"},{"time":627000,"text":"and they still disagree with us,"},{"time":629000,"text":"then we move on to a second assumption,"},{"time":631000,"text":"which is that they're idiots."},{"time":633000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":635000,"text":"They have all the right pieces of the puzzle,"},{"time":637000,"text":"and they are too moronic to put them together correctly."},{"time":640000,"text":"And when that doesn't work,"},{"time":642000,"text":"when it turns out that people who disagree with us"},{"time":645000,"text":"have all the same facts we do"},{"time":647000,"text":"and are actually pretty smart,"},{"time":650000,"text":"then we move on to a third assumption:"},{"time":653000,"text":"they know the truth,"},{"time":656000,"text":"and they are deliberately distorting it"},{"time":658000,"text":"for their own malevolent purposes."},{"time":662000,"text":"So this is a catastrophe."}]},{"cues":[{"time":664000,"text":"This attachment to our own rightness"},{"time":667000,"text":"keeps us from preventing mistakes"},{"time":669000,"text":"when we absolutely need to"},{"time":671000,"text":"and causes us to treat each other terribly."},{"time":675000,"text":"But to me, what's most baffling"},{"time":677000,"text":"and most tragic about this"},{"time":680000,"text":"is that it misses the whole point of being human."},{"time":684000,"text":"It's like we want to imagine"},{"time":686000,"text":"that our minds are just these perfectly translucent windows"},{"time":689000,"text":"and we just gaze out of them"},{"time":691000,"text":"and describe the world as it unfolds."},{"time":694000,"text":"And we want everybody else to gaze out of the same window"},{"time":696000,"text":"and see the exact same thing."},{"time":698000,"text":"That is not true,"},{"time":700000,"text":"and if it were, life would be incredibly boring."},{"time":703000,"text":"The miracle of your mind"},{"time":706000,"text":"isn't that you can see the world as it is."},{"time":710000,"text":"It's that you can see the world as it isn't."},{"time":714000,"text":"We can remember the past,"},{"time":716000,"text":"and we can think about the future,"},{"time":719000,"text":"and we can imagine what it's like"},{"time":721000,"text":"to be some other person in some other place."},{"time":724000,"text":"And we all do this a little differently,"},{"time":726000,"text":"which is why we can all look up at the same night sky"},{"time":728000,"text":"and see this"},{"time":730000,"text":"and also this"},{"time":732000,"text":"and also this."},{"time":735000,"text":"And yeah, it is also why we get things wrong."}]},{"cues":[{"time":739000,"text":"1,200 years before Descartes said his famous thing"},{"time":741000,"text":"about \"I think therefore I am,\""},{"time":743000,"text":"this guy, St. Augustine, sat down"},{"time":745000,"text":"and wrote \"Fallor ergo sum\" --"},{"time":748000,"text":"\"I err therefore I am.\""},{"time":752000,"text":"Augustine understood"},{"time":754000,"text":"that our capacity to screw up,"},{"time":756000,"text":"it's not some kind of embarrassing defect"},{"time":758000,"text":"in the human system,"},{"time":760000,"text":"something we can eradicate or overcome."},{"time":763000,"text":"It's totally fundamental to who we are."},{"time":766000,"text":"Because, unlike God,"},{"time":768000,"text":"we don't really know what's going on out there."},{"time":771000,"text":"And unlike all of the other animals,"},{"time":774000,"text":"we are obsessed with trying to figure it out."},{"time":778000,"text":"To me, this obsession"},{"time":780000,"text":"is the source and root"},{"time":782000,"text":"of all of our productivity and creativity."}]},{"cues":[{"time":785000,"text":"Last year, for various reasons,"},{"time":788000,"text":"I found myself listening to a lot of episodes"},{"time":790000,"text":"of the Public Radio show This American Life."},{"time":792000,"text":"And so I'm listening and I'm listening,"},{"time":795000,"text":"and at some point, I start feeling"},{"time":798000,"text":"like all the stories are about being wrong."},{"time":802000,"text":"And my first thought was,"},{"time":804000,"text":"\"I've lost it."},{"time":806000,"text":"I've become the crazy wrongness lady."},{"time":808000,"text":"I just imagined it everywhere,\""},{"time":810000,"text":"which has happened."},{"time":812000,"text":"But a couple of months later,"},{"time":814000,"text":"I actually had a chance to interview Ira Glass, who's the host of the show."},{"time":816000,"text":"And I mentioned this to him,"},{"time":818000,"text":"and he was like, \"No actually, that's true."},{"time":821000,"text":"In fact,\" he says,"},{"time":823000,"text":"\"as a staff, we joke"},{"time":825000,"text":"that every single episode of our show"},{"time":827000,"text":"has the same crypto-theme."},{"time":830000,"text":"And the crypto-theme is:"},{"time":832000,"text":"'I thought this one thing was going to happen"},{"time":835000,"text":"and something else happened instead.'"},{"time":838000,"text":"And the thing is,\" says Ira Glass, \"we need this."},{"time":841000,"text":"We need these moments"},{"time":843000,"text":"of surprise and reversal and wrongness"},{"time":845000,"text":"to make these stories work.\""},{"time":847000,"text":"And for the rest of us, audience members,"},{"time":849000,"text":"as listeners, as readers,"},{"time":852000,"text":"we eat this stuff up."},{"time":854000,"text":"We love things like plot twists"},{"time":857000,"text":"and red herrings and surprise endings."},{"time":860000,"text":"When it comes to our stories,"},{"time":863000,"text":"we love being wrong."}]},{"cues":[{"time":866000,"text":"But, you know, our stories are like this"},{"time":868000,"text":"because our lives are like this."},{"time":871000,"text":"We think this one thing is going to happen"},{"time":874000,"text":"and something else happens instead."},{"time":877000,"text":"George Bush thought he was going to invade Iraq,"},{"time":879000,"text":"find a bunch of weapons of mass destruction,"},{"time":881000,"text":"liberate the people and bring democracy to the Middle East."},{"time":885000,"text":"And something else happened instead."},{"time":888000,"text":"And Hosni Mubarak"},{"time":890000,"text":"thought he was going to be the dictator of Egypt for the rest of his life,"},{"time":892000,"text":"until he got too old or too sick"},{"time":894000,"text":"and could pass the reigns of power onto his son."},{"time":897000,"text":"And something else happened instead."},{"time":901000,"text":"And maybe you thought"},{"time":903000,"text":"you were going to grow up and marry your high school sweetheart"},{"time":905000,"text":"and move back to your hometown and raise a bunch of kids together."},{"time":909000,"text":"And something else happened instead."},{"time":912000,"text":"And I have to tell you"},{"time":914000,"text":"that I thought I was writing an incredibly nerdy book"},{"time":916000,"text":"about a subject everybody hates"},{"time":918000,"text":"for an audience that would never materialize."},{"time":921000,"text":"And something else happened instead."}]},{"cues":[{"time":923000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":925000,"text":"I mean, this is life."},{"time":927000,"text":"For good and for ill,"},{"time":929000,"text":"we generate these incredible stories"},{"time":932000,"text":"about the world around us,"},{"time":934000,"text":"and then the world turns around and astonishes us."},{"time":940000,"text":"No offense, but this entire conference"},{"time":943000,"text":"is an unbelievable monument"},{"time":945000,"text":"to our capacity to get stuff wrong."},{"time":947000,"text":"We just spent an entire week"},{"time":949000,"text":"talking about innovations and advancements"},{"time":951000,"text":"and improvements,"},{"time":953000,"text":"but you know why we need all of those innovations"},{"time":956000,"text":"and advancements and improvements?"},{"time":958000,"text":"Because half the stuff"},{"time":960000,"text":"that's the most mind-boggling and world-altering --"},{"time":963000,"text":"TED 1998 --"},{"time":965000,"text":"eh."},{"time":967000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":971000,"text":"Didn't really work out that way, did it?"},{"time":973000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":975000,"text":"Where's my jet pack, Chris?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":978000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":982000,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":987000,"text":"So here we are again."},{"time":990000,"text":"And that's how it goes."},{"time":992000,"text":"We come up with another idea."},{"time":994000,"text":"We tell another story."},{"time":997000,"text":"We hold another conference."},{"time":1000000,"text":"The theme of this one,"},{"time":1002000,"text":"as you guys have now heard seven million times,"},{"time":1004000,"text":"is the rediscovery of wonder."},{"time":1006000,"text":"And to me,"},{"time":1008000,"text":"if you really want to rediscover wonder,"},{"time":1011000,"text":"you need to step outside"},{"time":1013000,"text":"of that tiny, terrified space of rightness"},{"time":1019000,"text":"and look around at each other"},{"time":1022000,"text":"and look out at the vastness"},{"time":1025000,"text":"and complexity and mystery"},{"time":1028000,"text":"of the universe"},{"time":1031000,"text":"and be able to say,"},{"time":1034000,"text":"\"Wow, I don't know."},{"time":1038000,"text":"Maybe I'm wrong.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":1040000,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1042000,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1045000,"text":"Thank you guys."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1047000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}